_pause().details: called by the owner to pause, triggers stopped state

_unpause().details: called by the owner to unpause, returns to normal state

bid(uint256,uint256).details: Bids on an open sale, completing the sale and transferring

params._tokenId: - ID of token to bid on.

cancelSale(uint256).details: Cancels an sale that hasn't been won yet.  Returns the NFT to original owner.

cancelSaleWhenPaused(uint256).details: Cancels an sale when the contract is paused.  Only the owner may do this, and NFTs are returned to  the seller. This should only be used in emergencies.

params._tokenId: - ID of the NFT on sale to cancel.

createSale(uint256,uint256,address,uint2.details: Creates and begins a new sale.

params._seller: - Seller, if not the message sender
params._tokenId: - ID of token to sale, sender must be owner.

getSale(uint256).details: Returns sale info for an NFT on sale.

isOwner().details: Returns true if the caller is the current owner.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
